## What each file does

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `TextDetectionProcessor.java` | Wraps ML Kit — takes a Bitmap, returns `Text` result |
| `TextOverlayView.java` | Custom View — scales ML Kit bounding boxes to screen, draws AR-style labels |
| `MainActivity.java` | CameraX setup, capture trigger, wires detector → overlay |
| `activity_main.xml` | Preview + overlay stacked in a FrameLayout |

---

## Key things to know

- **`CAPTURE_MODE_MINIMIZE_LATENCY`** on ImageCapture makes the shutter as fast as possible
- The frozen frame is shown instantly while ML Kit processes in background — feels snappy
- `TextOverlayView` scales coordinates from image space → screen space so labels land exactly on the text
- Swap `TextRecognizerOptions.DEFAULT_OPTIONS` for `ChineseTextRecognizerOptions`, `DevanagariTextRecognizerOptions` etc. for other scripts — no other code changes needed